    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Two balanced three-phase loads, as shown in the figure, are connected to a $$100\\sqrt 3 $$ V, three-phase, 50 Hz main supply. Given Z<sub>1</sub> = (18 + j24) $$\\Omega$$ and Z<sub>2</sub> = (6 + j8) $$\\Omega$$. The ammeter reading, in amperes, is _________. (round off to nearest integer).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l73lg81f/fa17e1bc-1965-4d1e-ba0d-316a571d1910/5e6d6030-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lg81g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l73lg81f/fa17e1bc-1965-4d1e-ba0d-316a571d1910/5e6d6030-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lg81g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE EE 2022 Electrical and Electronics Measurement - Basic of Indicating Instruments Question 1 English\"></p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "20",
    "explanation": "<p>Convert $$\\Delta$$-Y<sub>Network</sub></p>\n<p>$$Z{'_1} = {{{Z_1} \\times {Z_1}} \\over {{Z_1} \\times {Z_1} \\times {Z_1}}} = {{{Z_1}} \\over 3} = {{18 + j24} \\over 3} = (6 + j8)\\,\\Omega $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l73lhs5w/1c35453e-0a70-4666-9404-95d399f6f866/89c85050-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lhs5x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l73lhs5w/1c35453e-0a70-4666-9404-95d399f6f866/89c85050-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lhs5x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE EE 2022 Electrical and Electronics Measurement - Basic of Indicating Instruments Question 1 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>After redrawing network,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l73lj36e/8539a46a-bfae-4800-afef-946758d96764/ae195760-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lj36f.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l73lj36e/8539a46a-bfae-4800-afef-946758d96764/ae195760-2175-11ed-82a2-1514197df0f1/file-1l73lj36f.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE EE 2022 Electrical and Electronics Measurement - Basic of Indicating Instruments Question 1 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$${Z_{eq}} = Z{'_1}||{Z_2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = (6 + j8)||(6 + j8)$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 3 + j4$$</p>\n<p>$${I_R} = {I_{Ph}} = {{{V_{RY}}} \\over {{Z_{eq}}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{100} \\over {3 + j4}} = 20\\,A$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
